name: Tsui’Goab
shortLoreBlurb: Tsui’Goab is a deity/hero from Khoikhoi associated with dawn, rain, battle with gaunab. Appeased for safe passage and rains.
overlapsLinks: Athena (Greek), Karttikeya (Hindu), Manannán (Celtic), Morrigan (Celtic), Naga (India/SE Asia), Poseidon (Greek), Sekhmet (Egyptian), Tangaroa (Polynesia), Yemaya (Yoruba)
description: Tsui’Goab is a deity/hero from Khoikhoi associated with dawn, rain, battle with gaunab. Appeased for safe passage and rains.
